discussion_comments.comment_body:
@sidharthv96, is removing this `throw e;` line in https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid/pull/4359/commits/16c12a42c7892eb268e4afdc9e9cf589ce9138a4 the expected behavior?

It seems like currently, the `mermaid.render()` function will render an error diagram, then throw an exception if the `diag.renderer.draw` function fails.

But now, it will only do that if `suppressErrorRendering: true`.

Would something like the following be better, since then by default, the behavior would be the same?

```ts
if (config.suppressErrorRendering) {
  removeTempElements();
} else {
  errorRenderer.draw(text, id, version);
}
throw e;
```

